<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-29T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="923" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d923">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">125.3516/10–2946: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-29T18:00:00-05:00">October 29,
                                1946—6 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>950. Since Dairen possesses appropriate receiving equipment for short wave
                        transmission, Department feels telegrams can be broadcast Dairen from
                        Shanghai or other location, communications officer Shanghai deems feasible,
                        on prearranged schedule basis. Although this method only provides means
                        sending telegrams to Dairen, Dept feels it worthwhile particularly in
                        notifying Dairen of courier and ship arrivals. Please take up with
                        communications officer and advise views. Sent Nanking, repeated
                        Shanghai.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>